{%- comment -%}
  Stockly — App embed ("Activate Stockly").

  The master on/off switch a merchant recognises from other apps
  (Sami, BSS, etc.): a single toggle under the theme editor's
  "App embeds" panel. Toggling it ON is how the merchant "activates"
  Stockly in their theme.

  What it does (intentionally light for v1):
  - Loads the shared `--sk-*` design tokens globally, so any Stockly
    storefront content renders on a consistent base across every page
    (the tokens are scoped to Stockly hosts, so this has no visual
    effect on the rest of the theme).
  - Exposes `window.__stocklyActive = true` so the admin Setup guide /
    future global scripts can confirm the app is switched on.

  No settings (toggle only) — matching the conventional "activate the
  app" pattern. Handle `stockly-embed` is what the admin Setup guide
  reads from the theme's settings_data.json to auto-detect activation.
{%- endcomment -%}

{{ 'stockly-base.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
<script>window.__stocklyActive = true;</script>

